☕︎ Just wasting time

     A corollary of this is that you can’t design a great product unless
     you live, eat, and breathe like your users do. You need to know
     exactly who your user is, what their problems are, how they perceive
     your product, and who helps them make buying decisions. Your
     intuition has to mirror how the customers will perceive your
     product. Categorizing features is only useful if it’s a good
     predictor of your actual users’s response. Otherwise, you’re just
     wasting time.

     How to build great products (cache)

   Today, I started a mission as a Product Owner. Both exciting and scary.

