☕︎ Emojis and evolution

     Speaking on Emoji Wrap in 2016, Google product manager Agustin Fonts
     was cautious about changing the Android gun emoji to match Apple’s
     new fluorescent green design, noting that they “want to be as
     compatible with other systems as possible”.

     Google Updates Gun Emoji (cache)

   Besides the cultural bias (cache) inherent to the interpretation of
   emojis themselves, be aware that the choices to represent these
   characters one way or the many others are left to operating systems
   companies and may completely change the conveyed message across time
   and platforms.

   Explicitness and perenialty are a constant challenge.

